The United States amends the rules for receiving a visa
The persons must present themselves to the service agencies for the visa application before their conversation at the Consulate; the costs will be shortened in this way.
On 10 January 2011, the procedures for the application for a visa in the U.S. Embassy and the Consulates will change.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves before their consultation at the consulate at the visa application service agencies (ASC, the original letters in English).
The staff of the ASC shall collect the applicant’s biometric data, which will be reviewed by the consulate before the conversation.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of the visa processing is reduced because it is no longer necessary to pay separately the deadline agreement, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is sent.
The applicant does only one payment that covers the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the countervalue is $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visa with application (including visa for time workers) and $390 for hands and investors.
Those who just want to extend their visa do not have to conduct a conversation at the consulate, they just have to present themselves at the next ASC, where they will present their documents and their fingerprints will be taken.
Since the biometric data is collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second date for the conversation in the consulate remain there less time than before.
Those who apply for a visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer have to pay the service fee of $26.
Further information on the new visa application procedure can be found on the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
